t 3 about D. We haven't asked about C. So we should ask both agents for C's calmness under pressure (we have keeps calm in crisis) but maybe ask about teamwork/communication more details. Also ask about candidate D's teamwork/communication more specifics.\n\nBut we already have some info: D is moody, loner, hot temper, know-it-all. That's negative. Might ask Agent 1 or 3 if they have any positive teamwork info for D.\n\nAlso we might ask about candidate A's calmness under pressure: maybe ask Agent 3.\n\nLet's decide: ask Agent 3: \"What can you tell me about Candidate A's calmness under pressure and teamwork/communication?\" Also ask Agent 1: \"What can you tell me about Candidate C's teamwork/communication skills and willingness to develop professionally?\" Also ask Agent 3: \"What can you tell me about Candidate D's teamwork/communication skills?\" But we have already asked Agent 3 about D's calmness and teamwork, they responded with no explicit info. So maybe ask Agent 1 for D? But we already asked Agent 3. Could ask Agent 1 for D's teamwork? Might get more.\n\nBut we have limited calls? Not limited. We'll ask both.\n\nWe also need to produce our public contribution summarizing current evidence, highlighting gaps, and maybe give provisional assessment leaning towards candidate C perhaps, but note concerns.\n\nWe need to output vote. At this point, we might be leaning to Candidate C because of calmness, quick correct decisions, technical understanding, but communication issues. Candidate B also strong but has nasty remarks and weak memory for numbers (maybe not critical). Candidate D has temperament issues. Candidate A lacks calmness info.\n\nThus likely candidate C is best despite communication issues; but we need to verify if communication can be mitigated. So we might ask for more info on C's communication and teamwork.\n\nThus our vote maybe Candidate C, but we can also be undecided until we get more info. The instruction: \"If you cannot yet choose a candidate based on the available evidence, vote Undecided.\" We have enough to make a provisional but we might want to ask more. However we have some info: C has difficulty communicating ideas (negative), egocentric (negative), not willing to further education (negative). Those are significant. B also has negative: nasty remarks, weak memory for numbers, uncooperative. D has hot temper, know-it-all, moody, loner. A has show-off, not open to new ideas, no calmness info. So all have negatives. Which negatives are most serious for safety? Communication and teamwork are critical. C's difficulty communicating and egocentric may be severe. B's nasty remarks and uncooperative also severe. D's hot temper and moody also severe. A's show-off and not open to new ideas also problematic.\n\nWe need to weigh strengths: C's calmness, quick decisions, technical. B's stress handling, conscientious, weather assessment, computer skills. D's problem solving, responsibility, concentration. A's anticipation, spatial vision, leadership.\n\nWhich combination best? Long-distance flights require calmness, decision-making, technical, teamwork. B's stress handling is good, but communication issues. C's calmness and decision-making are strong, but communication issues. D's problem solving and responsibility but temperament. A's anticipation and leadership but unknown calmness.\n\nProbably candidate B's stress handling and conscientiousness may outweigh communication issues if they can improve. But B also makes nasty remarks, which could harm crew morale. That seems serious.\n\nCandidate C's calmness and quick correct decisions are crucial for emergencies. Communication difficulty could be mitigated with training, but egocentric may hinder crew cooperation.\n\nGiven the data, I think candidate C might be the best overall despite communication issues, because calmness and decision-making are paramount. But we need more info on communication to be sure.\n\nThus we could vote Candidate C but note we need more info. Or we could vote Undecided pending more info. The instruction: \"If you cannot yet choose a candidate based on the available evidence, vote Undecided.\" We have enough to make a choice, but we are uncertain. I think we can give provisional vote for Candidate C, but we can also ask for more info before final. However we must output vote now. We can still vote Candidate C.\n\nLet's produce public message summarizing evidence, highlighting gaps, and stating vote for Candidate C with confidence maybe 60%."}
