d to give our vote. Based on current evidence, we likely still vote Candidate C. But we should consider if any new info could change. We have no positive for A, D, B. So C remains best. So vote Candidate C.\n\nThus produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE: answer about A, maybe note we have no positive info, only negative (unfriendly, leadership). Also note we have no explicit calmness info. Then ask targeted question to agent_1: any positive info about D's teamwork/communication? Also maybe ask agent_1 about any positive info about A's calmness under pressure (though we are answering that). Actually we are answering that, so no need to ask again. Could ask agent_1 for any positive info about A's calmness. But we can answer: we have no positive info. So we can ask if they have any.\n\nThus final: PUBLIC_MESSAGE includes answer and question(s). Then METADATA_JSON with vote.\n\nProceed."}
